# Solidity Compiler Backend Server

This server provides a backend API for compiling Solidity smart contracts. It includes the OpenZeppelin library, making it easy to compile standard contracts such as ERC20 and ERC721.

## Installation

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run the server in development mode
npm run dev

# Run the server in production mode
npm start

# Environment Variables
PORT: Server port (default: 3001)

FRONTEND_URL: Allowed frontend URL for CORS (default: http://localhost:3000)

API Endpoints
POST /compile
Compiles Solidity source code.